"```sql\nSELECT MAX(L.Date) AS LatestMedicalDataDate\nFROM Patient P\nJOIN Laboratory L ON P.ID = L.ID\nWHERE P.First_Date = (\n    SELECT MAX(First_Date)\n    FROM Patient\n)\nAND L.LDH >= 500;\n```\n\nThis SQL query finds the latest date of medical data recorded for the patient with the most recent first date of hospital visit, who also has an abnormal level of lactate dehydrogenase (LDH >= 500). The query joins the `Patient` and `Laboratory` tables using the `ID` foreign key relationship and filters based on the conditions specified in the evidence."